t: When*p Israel went out of Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people of strange language;
Judah*p was his sanctuary, and Israel his dominion.
The*p sea saw it, and fled: Jordan was driven back.
The*p mountains skipped like rams, and the little hills like lambs.
What*p ailed thee, O thou sea, that thou fleddest? thou Jordan, that thou wast driven back?
Ye*p mountains, that ye skipped like rams; and ye little hills, like lambs?
Tremble,*p thou earth, at the presence of the Lord, at the presence of the God of Jacob;
Which*p turned the rock into a standing water, the flint into a fountain of waters.
